{{Infobox musical artist |name = Bheems Ceciroleo |background = solo_singer |image = |caption = |native_name = భీమస్ సెసిరోలె |native_name_lang = |birth_name = |alias = |birth_date = <!-- Please cite a reliable source for date of birth --> |birth_place = [[Jalore District]], [[Rajasthan]], India |occupation = [[Music composer]], Singer, [[Lyricist]] and Director |instrument = |years_active = 2003–present |website = |imagesize = }} '''Bheems Ceciroleo''' is an Indian [[music composer]], [[lyricist]], singer, and director.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.moviebuff.com/bheems-ceciroleo|title= Bheems Ceciroleo, music director|work=Movie Buff|date=3 January 2017|accessdate=31 August 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.filmibeat.com/celebs/bheems-music-director/filmography.html|title=Bheems Ceciroleo Filmography|work=filmibeat|date=3 January 2017|accessdate=31 August 2015}}</ref> He is best known for his works in [[Telugu cinema]]. He became an overnight sensation as a lyricist with "Oye Raju" from the film, [[Aayudham (2003 film)|Aayudham]]. [[Bengal Tiger]] is the biggest film of his career so far.
