{{Orphan|date=October 2016}}
[[File:Obywatel Włapko.jpg|thumb|Citizen Skimmer (''Polish: Obywatel Włapko'') - the symbol of corrupt official]] '''Citizen Włapko''' (''Citizen Skimmer, Polish: Obywatel Włapko'') - the symbol of corrupt official, hindering a man's life.<ref>{{cite web|title=Powstanie pomnik pana Włapko, symbolu łapownictwa?|url=http://tvp3.tvp.pl/24510793/powstanie-pomnik-pana-wlapko-symbolu-lapownictwa|agency=Telewizja TVP3 Szczecin|date=20 March 2016}}</ref> Sculpture, a satirical figure shows a naked boy with the head of a mature man wearing glasses with a mustache and beard, with hands arranged in such a way as if the finger of the right hand was pointing to it and asking for somebody to give him something into the other hand.
It is 1.10 meters high. There is a bomb next to his left foot, which symbolizes its explosive nature, and the nudity symbolizes the whole, "naked" truth.
The creator of the sculpture is [[Wiesław Adamski]] from [[Szczecinek]], [[Poland]]. The satirical figure was presented for the first time during the Happening on June 25, 2015 in [[Szczecinek]], and then it visited many cities throughout the country.<ref>{{cite web|title=Obywatel Włapko zwiedził całą Polskę. W poniedziałek będzie na sesji Rady Miasta|url=http://iszczecinek.pl/artykuly/felietony/obywatel-wlapko-zwiedzil-cala-polske-w-poniedzialek-bedzie-na-sesji-rady-miasta|agency=iszczecinek.pl|date=27 August 2016}}</ref>
One of the city's officials personally rendered justice to the author of the sculpture assaulting the artist in front of his apartment.<ref>{{cite web|title=Miejski konserwator zabytków wymierzył sprawiedliwość artyście|url=http://iszczecinek.pl/artykuly/aktualnosci/miejski-konserwator-zabytkow-wymierzyl-sprawiedliwosc-artyscie|agency=iszczecinek.pl|date=29 June 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Afera w Szczecinku. Urzędnik pobił się z artystą o rzeźbę|url=http://www.fakt.pl/wydarzenia/polska/afera-w-szczecinku-urzednik-pobil-sie-z-artysta-o-rzezbe/wq8rlh8|agency=FAKT24.pl|date=14 July 2015}}</ref>
The Social Monument Building Committee of Citizen Włapko was created in [[Szczecinek]], with the goal of constructing the monument in the city.<ref>{{cite web|title=Nie chcą, ale muszą. Radni zajmą się Obywatelem Włapko|url=http://iszczecinek.pl/artykuly/aktualnosci/nie-chca-ale-musza-radni-zajma-sie-obywatelem-wlapko|agency=iszczecinek.pl|date=2 August 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Pomnik skorumpowanego urzędnika|url=http://teleexpress.tvp.pl/24521288/pomnik-skorumpowanego-urzednika|agency=Telewizja TVP-Teleexpress|date=21 March 2016}}</ref>
During the session of the City Council in [[Szczecinek]], the poster with the image of Citizen Włapko caused confusion, when the councillor, Jacek Pawłowicz, with the support of the councillor Andrzej Grobelny, tried to give the poster for the mayor. The poster was not accepted by the mayor, and he took two councillors to court.<ref>{{cite web|title=Burmistrz podaje radnych do sądu. Za plakat|url=http://temat.net/aktualnosci/25122/Burmistrz-podaje-radnych-do-sadu.-Za-plakat|agency=Temat szczecinecki.pl|date=14 April 2016}}</ref>
