[[File:Philippines HDI map.svg|thumb|450px|The [[Human Development Index|HDI values]] for all [[provinces of the Philippines]]. (2009 map)]]
This is a list of [[provinces of the Philippines]], including Metro Manila, in order of their [[Human Development Index]] (HDI).

==Methodology==
The HDI values are provided by the Human Development Network (HDN) of the Philippines<ref name="PH_HDN">[https://psa.gov.ph/sites/default/files/HDI%20Tables%2C%20final%2015jan16_0_0.pdf Table 1. Human Development Index and Its Components: 2012] ''[[Philippine Human Development Network]]''</ref> and have been updated as of 2012.

==Highs and lows==
All [[Provinces of the Philippines|provinces]] surrounding Metro Manila have a '''<span style="color:#00CC00">high</span>''' HDI value. Metro Manila, Benguet, and Rizal already have '''<span style="color:	#00A550">very high</span>''' HDI values (>0.800). The southern region of [[Mindanao]] has three of the provinces with the lowest ('''<span style="color:#990000">low</span>''') HDI values (<0.500).<ref name="PH_HDN"/>

